# 🛠 Windows Admin Toolkit

A Python-based admin toolkit for Windows system analysis and automation. Designed for system triage and audit tasks using built-in tools, registry access, and `pywin32`.

## ✅ Prerequisites

Run the following in **PowerShell as Administrator**:

```powershell
pip install pywin32 colorama

Then verify:
python -c "import win32evtlog, colorama; print('✔ ok')"

 Available Tasks
Use the --task flag to run one of the following tools:

Task Flag	Description
win-events	View failed/successful login events from Security logs
win-pkgs	List all installed software with optional CSV export
win-services	Check and optionally restart Windows services
win-startup ✅	🔍 NEW: Show startup programs from registry (HKCU\\...\\Run)
win-firewall ✅	🔥 NEW: List inbound firewall rules allowing 0.0.0.0/0 traffic

🧪 Usage Examples
🔐 Failed logons (last 12 hours, 3+ attempts)
python analyze_windows.py --task win-events --hours 12 --min-count 3

Installed software audit (export to CSV)
python analyze_windows.py --task win-pkgs --csv pkgs.csv

🔧 Ensure critical services are running
python analyze_windows.py --task win-services --watch Spooler wuauserv --fix

 List startup programs (from registry)
 python analyze_windows.py --task win-startup

🧱 Show risky inbound firewall rules
python analyze_windows.py --task win-firewall
